An elderly man was bitten on the leg by a crocodile at the Palmer Sea Reef Golf Course in Port Douglas on Monday afternoon . 
  John Lahiff believes he accidentally stood on a sunbaking crocodile . 
  He received puncture wounds on his leg and foot and was taken to Cairns Base Hospital . 
  Mr Lahiff says he will return to the course to play golf again . 
  Clive Palmer owns the course and says the crocodile has been removed from the course . 
  The man was treated at the scene and taken to hospital . 
 